---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Rwanda Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/rwanda/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Kenya for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kenya' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'Tanzania for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/tanzania' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'rwandaFit', header: 'Rwanda Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RWF$380,000-543,000/mo', rwandaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RWF$445,000-635,000/mo', rwandaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RWF$342,000-488,000/mo', rwandaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RWF$317,000-453,000/mo', rwandaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (RSSB, Soras)', entryAge: 'Varies', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'RWF$50,000-150,000/mo', rwandaFit: 'Basic' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'RWF$342K-543K', annual: 'RWF$4.1M-6.5M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'RWF$469K-724K', annual: 'RWF$5.6M-8.7M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'RWF$631K-973K', annual: 'RWF$7.6M-11.7M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'RWF$30K-80K/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'RWF$150K-400K/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Rwanda 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Rwanda. Clean, safe, improving healthcare, gorilla trekking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Rwanda"
  subheadline="Rwanda offers Africa's cleanest cities, exceptional safety, improving healthcare, stunning landscapes, and efficient governance—a transformed nation attracting adventurous retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/rwanda-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Rwanda</h2>
  <p>
    Rwanda offers remarkable transformation—from 1994 tragedy to Africa's safest, cleanest country. Efficient governance, excellent infrastructure, improving healthcare, and stunning "Land of a Thousand Hills" beauty attract adventurous retirees seeking something different.
  </p>

  <p>
    Kigali is the capital with best healthcare and remarkably clean streets. Musanze provides gateway to gorilla trekking. Lake Kivu offers resort lifestyle. Nyungwe Forest has biodiversity. Most retirees choose Kigali for services; explore country for experiences.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving rapidly; good private options in Kigali</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Kinyarwanda, English, French</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> RWF$800K-1.6M/month (~$700-1,400 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Highland tropical; mild year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Clean; safe; efficient; transformed</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Africa's safest country</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Rwanda Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Rwanda healthcare is improving rapidly—King Faisal Hospital Kigali is leading facility (referral hospital). Polyclinique de l'Etoile and private clinics offer good care. Healthcare investment is national priority. Complex cases may need Nairobi, Johannesburg, or international evacuation.
  </p>

  <p>
    Universal health insurance (Mutuelle de Santé) covers most population—impressive achievement. Private care is affordable and improving. Kigali has best options; regional healthcare is basic. International insurance with evacuation recommended for comprehensive security.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Improving Rapidly</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Rwanda healthcare is improving faster than most African countries. New hospitals under construction. Specialty care expanding. However, complex cases still need evacuation to Nairobi or South Africa. International insurance with strong evacuation essential.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Rwanda has accessible visa policies:
  </p>

  <h3>Visa on Arrival</h3>
  <p>
    30-day visa on arrival for all nationalities (part of Africa opening). Simple and quick. Extensions available.
  </p>

  <h3>East African Visa</h3>
  <p>
    90-day multi-country visa for Rwanda, Kenya, Uganda. Good for exploring region.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories including retirement. Application through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    After qualifying period. Investment route available. Rwanda welcomes foreign investment.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Rwanda:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> No insurance required for short stays</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Include Nairobi/Johannesburg coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Rwanda</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with regional evacuation coverage essential. Nairobi (1-hour flight) and Johannesburg provide backup. Kigali healthcare improving but not yet comprehensive. Local coverage affordable but limited for complex needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Rwanda, evacuation coverage important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Rwanda</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Africa network, excellent evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Nairobi access:</strong> Key regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>Improving locally:</strong> Kigali care getting better</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with strong Africa evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Rwanda (RWF ~1,140 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Kigali base:</strong> Best healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Mutuelle:</strong> Local coverage supplement</li>
    <li><strong>Regional network:</strong> Nairobi for complex care</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Development Worker, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month pension. Temp residence. Kigali.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global comprehensive with Africa focus.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~RWF$450,000/month (~$395). Purpose-driven retirement; regional backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Belgian Francophone, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,400/month pension. Residence permit. Lake Kivu.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Europe and Africa coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~RWF$580,000/month (~$510). Francophone ease; Belgium backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Kenyan Neighbor, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month income. EAC movement. Kigali.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care regional with Nairobi backup.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~RWF$370,000/month (~$325). Regional ease; home country backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Rwanda really that safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—consistently ranked Africa's safest country. Very low crime. Walking safe at night. Efficient police. Strict laws enforced. Plastic bags banned since 2008 (environmental pioneer). Transformation is genuine and remarkable.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is it really clean?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Remarkably clean—monthly community cleaning (Umuganda) maintains standards. No plastic bags. Clean streets. National pride in cleanliness. Kigali is notably cleaner than many Western cities. Not what you might expect.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What language do I need?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        English or French work—both are official (along with Kinyarwanda). English increasingly dominant in business and government since 2008 shift. French still common. Healthcare providers typically multilingual.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the history?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        1994 genocide is part of Rwanda's story—memorials are important and moving. Country has deliberately transformed. Reconciliation is ongoing national process. History is acknowledged; focus is on future. Safe to discuss respectfully.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Rwanda coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Rwanda authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
